{{ill|Nichu Shrine|ja|日雲神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nichu Shrine|qq=}} is a {{ill|Moto-Ise Shrines|lt=Motoise shrine|ja|元伊勢|1=Moto-Ise Shrines|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moto-Ise Shrines|13=User:Immanuelle/Moto-Ise Shrines|qq=}}.

Moto-Ise Shrines are [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrines]] that used to host Amaterasu before she was moved to [[:en:Ise Shrine|Ise Jingu]]. The first one was {{ill|Hibara Shrine|ja|檜原神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hibara Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大神神社}} ([[:en:Ōmiwa Shrine|Ōmiwa Shrine]]).

*
==Overview==
{{神社
|名称=日雲神社
|image=[[File:Hikumo-jinja.JPG|250px]]<br />日雲神社　拝殿
|所在地=[[:en:Shiga Prefecture|Shiga Prefecture]][[:en:Kōka, Shiga|Koka City]] 信楽町牧75
|位置={{ウィキ座標2段度分秒|34|54|28.4|N|136|05|00.1|E|region:JP-25_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}
|祭神={{ill|Ame-no-Minakanushi|ja|天御中主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Minakanushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天之御中主神}}
|社格={{ill|village shrine|ja|村社|lt=Son-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#Village_shrines|lt=former village shrine|lt_ja=旧村社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/village shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度}}
|創建=Founding date unknown
|本殿=Three-bay shrine [[:en:Nagare-zukuri|Nagare-zukuri]]
|例祭=[[:en:May 5|May 5]]
|神事=Taiko Dance
}}
'''Nichu Shrine''' (日雲神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located at 75 Makimachi, Shigaraki, [[:en:Kōka, Shiga|Koka City]], [[:en:Shiga Prefecture|Shiga Prefecture]].

== {{nihongo|Worshipped Deities|祭神|Saijin}} ==
* {{ill|Ame-no-Minakanushi|ja|天御中主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Minakanushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天之御中主神}}

== Shrine Emblem ==
* Ume Bowl (梅鉢)

== History ==
Although its founding date is unknown, the origin is traditionally attributed to the {{ill|Moto-Ise Shrines|ja|元伊勢|1=Moto-Ise Shrines|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Moto-Ise Shrines|13=User:Immanuelle/Moto-Ise Shrines|qq=}} "'''Koka-Hikumo Shrine''' (甲可日雲宮)" recorded in {{ill|Shinto Gobu-sho|ja|神道五部書|lt=Ise Shinto Gobu-sho|lt_ja=伊勢神道五部書|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto Gobu-sho|qq=}} and the chronicle {{ill|Yamato Hime no Mikoto Chronicles|ja|倭姫命世記|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Hime no Mikoto Chronicles|qq=}}. The main hall is said to have been constructed in [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 4 (1691). It was once known as "Uenoyama Tenjin" and "Makimura Tenmangu", but in [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 18 (1885) its name was changed to the current one. The precincts are traversed by the [[:en:Shigaraki Kohgen Railway|Shigaraki Kogen Railway]]. In [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 9 (1876) it was listed as a {{ill|village shrine|ja|村社|lt=Son-sha|1=Modern_system_of_ranked_Shinto_shrines#Village_shrines|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/village shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度}}.

== Festivals ==
* Annual Festival: May 5

== Cultural Properties ==
* Main Hall – A three-bay shrine structure in the [[:en:Nagare-zukuri|Nagare-zukuri]] style with a cypress bark roof {{ill|Cypress bark roof|ja|檜皮葺|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Cypress bark roof|qq=}}, said to have been constructed in [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 4 (1691). It is registered as a National {{ill|Registered tangible cultural property|ja|登録有形文化財|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Registered tangible cultural property|qq=}} as a representative example of the Nagare-zukuri tradition in Ōmi since the medieval period.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|title=Koka City History Vol.8 Koka City Encyclopedia|date=2016-12-12|year=2016|publisher=Koka City}}</ref>
* Hexagonal Stone Lantern – Possessing an inscription from the [[:en:Kamakura period|Kamakura period]], [[:en:Kagen|Kagen]] 4 (1306), designated as a cultural property by Koka City.
* Taiko Dance – Selected intangible {{ill|Folk Cultural Property|ja|民俗文化財|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Folk Cultural Property|qq=}} of Shiga Prefecture.

== Shrine Auxiliary Facilities ==
* On-site Shrines
** {{ill|Hachiman shrine|lt=Hachiman shrine|lt=Hachiman Shrine|ja|八幡神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 八幡宮}}
** {{ill|Kasuga-taisha|lt=Kasuga-taisha|lt=Kasuga Shrine|ja|春日神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kasuga Shrine|qq=}}
** {{ill|Amemiya Shrine|ja|雨宮神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amemiya Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
** [[:en:Itsukushima Shrine|Itsukushima Shrine]]
* Off-site Shrines
** {{ill|Kashima Jingu|lt=Kashima Jingu|lt=Kashima Shrine|ja|鹿島神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kashima Shrine|qq=}}

== Access ==
* A 5‑minute walk from [[:en:Shigaraki Kohgen Railway|Shigaraki Kogen Railway]]’s [[:en:Kumoi Station|Unoi Station]]

